      </font><a href='brew_rec.asp'><font color='#000071'>Item
      Table </font></a><font color='#0e024d' face='Arial'> &nbsp; |&nbsp; </font><a href='brew_vend.asp'><font color='#000071'>Supply
      Vendors&nbsp;</font></a><font color='#0e024d' face='Arial'> |</font></font></b></p>
      <hr SIZE='1' width='90%'>
        <table border='0' width='90%'>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td align='left' vAlign='top'><font face='Arial' color='#0e024d' size='2'><b>Overview</b></font>
                <p><font face='Arial' size='2'>Brewing is one of the easiest and
                cheapest trade skills to master.&nbsp; Most of the supplies
                needed to brew generally sell for a gold piece or less and
                others may be obtained through looting and foraging.&nbsp; Of
                course, the flip side to this is the fact that no one has in
                Norrath has ever gotten wealthy from the money gained through
                brewing.&nbsp; Aside from the roleplaying aspects - the crowds
                seem to be more impressed when they see you chugging Bleeding
                Brains rather than the ubiquitous Dwarven Ale - brewing is used
                to make some products used by other tradesmen and by those
                adventurers seeking to complete some quests.&nbsp; However, many
                people take up brewing just for the enjoyment they get from
                watching their alcohol tolerance rise from drinks they made with
                their own two hands.</font></p>
                <p><strong><font color='#0e024d' face='Arial' size='2'>Brewing a
                Drink</font></strong></p>
                <p><font face='Arial' size='2'>Brewing is rather simple.&nbsp;
                You need a container of some sort (Bottle, Cask, or Shot Glass),
                some ingredients to brew together, and a Brewing Barrel (looks
                like a Still) to brew your concoction in.&nbsp; Every city in
                Norrath has a Brewing Barrel with the exception of Grobb (Note:
                not sure about Paineel). As there are no &quot;portable&quot;
                Brewing Barrels,&nbsp; aspiring Troll brewers must leave home to
                follow this calling.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; You place your container
                and ingredients into the Brewing Barrel (making sure that
                nothing is stacked, if the recipe calls for Short Beer (2) place
                one beer in each of two slots) and hit combine.&nbsp; If you are
                successful you will receive one or more beverages.&nbsp; If not,
                you will lose your ingredients but will keep the container for
                another try</font></p>
                <p><font face='Arial' size='2'>Once
                you start brewing successfully, you will find few uses for your
                goods other than to drink them yourself or give them away to
                friends and strangers.&nbsp; The few exceptions are as
                follows:&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
                <ul>
                  <li><font face='Arial'><strong><font color='#000071' size='2'>Bog
                Juices:</font></strong><font size='2'> are used by Paladins in their quest to
                retrieve the sword Soulfire.</font></font></li>
                  <li><font face='Arial'><strong><font color='#000071' size='2'>Tumpy
                Tonics:</font></strong><font size='2'><font color='#000071'> </font> are used by Rangers in their quest to
                retrieve the bow Trueshot and by others questing to slate
                Groflah Steadfast's thirst.</font></font></li>
                  <li><font face='Arial'><strong><font color='#000071' size='2'>Heady
                Kiolas:</font></strong><font size='2'> are used by Tailors to cure their silk.</font></font></li>
                  <li><font size='2' face='Arial'><strong><font color='#000071'>Gnomish Spirits:</font></strong>
                    are used by those industrious
                Gnomish Tinkerers to create Firewater.</font></li>
                </ul>
                <p><strong><font color='#0e024d' face='Arial' size='2'>Skill
                Building</font></strong></p>
                <p><font face='Arial' size='2'>It isn't
                necessary to put any skill points at all into brewing.&nbsp;
                Just keep banging out Bog Juices and you should soon get your
                first point and be on your way to becoming a Brewmaster.&nbsp;&nbsp; </font></p>
                <p><font face='Arial' size='2'>
                Keep making Bog Juice until you reach skill 21, then switch to
                short beer.&nbsp; One of the fastest and easiest paths to
                becoming a master is to set up base in West Freeport and use
                the following progression:&nbsp; </font></p>
                <ol>
                  <li><font face='Arial' size='2'> Bog Juice </font></li>
                  <li><font face='Arial' size='2'>Short Beer </font></li>
                  <li><font face='Arial' size='2'>Mead </font></li>
                  <li><font face='Arial' size='2'>Short Ale </font></li>
                  <li><font face='Arial' size='2'>Ale</font></li>
                  <li><font face='Arial' size='2'> Ol' Tujim's Fierce Brew </font></li>
                  <li><font face='Arial' size='2'>Ginesh</font></li>
                </ol>
                <p><font face='Arial' size='2'> The snake
                scales needed for the Bog Juice can be bought at the first hut
                in the East Commonlands.&nbsp; After skill 21, you can go all
                the way to skill 135 with Ol' Tumjins without ever leaving the
                West Freeport Zone.&nbsp; Buy your ingredients from Krystin
                Charcoal, your Containers from the Hog Callers Inn, and use the
                Brew Barrel right in front of the Hog Callers Inn.&nbsp;&nbsp; </font></p>
                <p><font face='Arial' size='2'> Note
                that to follow this path you must be on Antonica.&nbsp; The
                ingredients needed for most of those drinks cannot be found in
                Faydwer or Odus.&nbsp; The final brew requires the help of a
                Ranger or Druid or time spent shopping on the secondary
                market.&nbsp; You'll need hundreds of foraged vegetables to use
                brewing Ginesh before you will finally reach the apex of our
                craft at skill 168 - currently the highest attainable level for
                Brewing. </font></p>
                <p><font face='Arial' size='2'>Note:&nbsp; <strong><font color='#0E024D'>Elven
                Wine</font><font color='#008000'> </font> </strong>has never been made, as no one has
                ever been able to find Morning Dew.&nbsp; If you find it, please
                let us know.</font></p>
              </td>
